<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9546] Annotations on class signature are rendered incorrectly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9546</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I have an annotated class, generated groovydoc contains a link to the annotation and appended annotation name just after it as in following screenshot:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13002546/13002546_image-2020-05-10-17-47-00-858.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After some debugging, I managed to fix the issue by modifying&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
org/codehaus/groovy/tools/groovydoc/gstringTemplates/classLevel/classDocName.html.annotations()&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;def annotations = { t, sepChar -&amp;gt;
    // t.annotations() ? t.annotations().collect{ it.isTypeAvailable() ? &apos;@&apos; + linkable(it.type().typeName()) + (it.description() - (&apos;@&apos;+it.type().typeName())) : it.description()}.join(sepChar) + sepChar : &apos;&apos;
    t.annotations() ? t.annotations().collect{ it.isTypeAvailable() ? &apos;@&apos; + linkable(it.type().typeName()) : it.description()}.join(sepChar) + sepChar : &apos;&apos;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
